y). Just type\n\n<code>scp fileToBeUploaded CRSid@shell.srcf.net:/public/societies/cuuass/destination</code>\n\nand enter your password. After uploading, be sure to set the correct file permissions (see next section)!\n\n==File Permissions==\nAfter uploading files to the server you should make sure that the correct file permissions are set. If you don\'t know about Linux file permissions, check out the permissions chapter in [http://www.linuxcommand.org/tlcl.php The Linux Command Line]. For regular files, reasonable permissions are 660. Every cuuass administrator is part of the cuuass group and files should be writable for everybody, thus group write permissions are recommended. To se the correct permissions, the kind people at SRFC have written a bash script that does just that. To execute this script, simply type <code>srcf-soc-permfix cuuass</code>. The script does the following:\n* finds files in <code>/public/societies/$socname</code> that do not belong to the group <code>$socname</code> and changes their group to <code>$socname</code>,\n* finds files in <code>/public/societies/$socname</code> which do not have group read and write permissions and adds those permissions,\n* finds directories in <code>/public/societies/$socname</code> that do not have the setgid bit set and sets the setgid bit.\nIf something is working fine on your local machine but not on the server, chances are that the permissions are wrong. It is recommended to always run the SRCF\'s script after uploading something to the server via <code>scp</code>.\n\n=FAQ=\nBe sure to check out the [https://www.srcf.net/faq/ SRCF\'s FAQ].\n\n=Security of the Wiki=\nThis wiki uses [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/MediaWiki MediaWiki], the same software package on which Wikipedia runs. The installation can be found under </code>/wiki/</code>. For this wiki, file uploads are enabled. This poses a potential security risk. To ensure that users cannot do damage by uploading malicious scripts, the upload directo