 this guide] to create a backup and upload it to our [https://github.com/CUUASS/WebsitePlusWiki GitHub repo]. This script resides under <code>/public/societies/cuuass/scripts/</code>:\n\n<syntaxhighlight lang=\"bash\">\n#!/bin/bash\n\n# first create Database dump\necho \'$wgReadOnly = \"Dumping Database, Access will be restored shortly\"\' \\\n        >> /public/societies/cuuass/public_html/wiki/LocalSettings.php\n\n# nice -n 19 lowers the priority of the process\nnice -n 19 mysqldump -h localhost -u cuuass -p --default-character-set=binary cuuass --password=\"outSecretMySqlPassword\" \\\n        > /public/societies/cuuass/public_html/wiki_backup/backup.sql\n\n# remove last line from LocalSettings.php which was added above\n# thus restoring write access to wiki\nsed -i \'$ d\' /public/societies/cuuass/public_html/wiki/LocalSettings.php\n\n# Now do a git commit and push to github\ncd /public/societies/cuuass/public_html/\nnice -n 19 git add -A\ngit commit -m \"This is an automatic commit, created on $(date)\"\ngit push\necho \"done\"\ncd -\n</syntaxhighlight>\n\nAgain, this script must have permissions 660 so the password is not world-readable. The user <code>rnw29</code> installed a [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron cronjob] for this script that runs every Monday at 4:30am.\n\nYou might be worried that the SQL dump also contains passwords of wiki users, however these passwords are [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptographic_hash_function hashed] using a [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salt_(cryptography) random salt], which would make it difficult for an attacker to find out the passwords.',_binary 'utf-8'),(17,_binary 'If no dedicated SysAdmin was elected then the President is responsible for the tasks detailed on this site. Ideally a SysAdmin should have some knowledge of the Linux command line, though there is nothing that can\'t be learned. Check out [http://www.linuxcommand.org/tlcl.php this free book] (free in all senses of the word), which should answer mos