sions==\nAfter uploading files to the server you should make sure that the correct file permissions are set. If you don\'t know about Linux file permissions, check out the permissions chapter in [http://www.linuxcommand.org/tlcl.php The Linux Command Line]. For regular files, reasonable permissions are 660. Every cuuass administrator is part of the cuuass group and files should be writable for everybody, thus group write permissions are recommended. To se the correct permissions, the kind people at SRFC have written a bash script that does just that. To execute this script, simply type <code>srcf-soc-permfix cuuass</code>. The script does the following:\n* finds files in <code>/public/societies/$socname</code> that do not belong to the group <code>$socname</code> and changes their group to <code>$socname</code>,\n* finds files in <code>/public/societies/$socname</code> which do not have group read and write permissions and adds those permissions,\n* finds directories in <code>/public/societies/$socname</code> that do not have the setgid bit set and sets the setgid bit.\nIf something is working fine on your local machine but not on the server, chances are that the permissions are wrong. It is recommended to always run the SRCF\'s script after uploading something to the server via <code>scp</code>.\n\n==FAQ==\nBe sure to check out the [https://www.srcf.net/faq/ SRCF\'s FAQ].\n\n=The Wiki=\n==Security of the Wiki==\nThis wiki uses [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/MediaWiki MediaWiki], the same software package on which Wikipedia runs. The installation can be found under </code>/wiki/</code>. For this wiki, file uploads are enabled. This poses a potential security risk. To ensure that users cannot do damage by uploading malicious scripts, the upload directory needs to have server-side execution of PHP scripts disabled, see [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:Security#Upload_security here]. The corresponding <code>.htaccess</code> file is [https://github.com/CUUASS/WebsitePlusWiki/blob/618ab3550b0a9c7c5a8ed4ab9dbdb1ddf48bb3e8/wiki/images/.htaccess here].\n\nThe main wiki settings are stored in <code>/wiki/LocalSettings.php</code>. By default this is also the location of our MySQL database password (the corresponding PHP variable is <code>$wgDBpassword</code>). This is clearly not a good idea as PHP scripts can become visible to plain text through the web in certain circumstances. It is recommended to keep all kinds of passwords outside of the webroot. For this purpose the directory <code>/public/societies/cuuass/external_includes</code> was created, which contains the script <code>mysql_pw.php</code> (which contains the MySQL password). The script is of the form\n\n<syntaxhighlight lang=\"php\">\n<?php\n        $wgDBtype = \"mysql\";\n        $wgDBname = \"cuuass\";\n        $wgDBserver = \"localhost\";\n        $wgDBuser = \"cuuass\";\n        $wgDBpassword = \"ourSecretMySqlPassword\";\n?>\n</syntaxhighlight>\n\nRemember to change <code>ourSecretMySqlPassword</code> when you copy this. This script \'\'\'must not be world readable\'\'\' so that other users of the server cannot see our MySQL password (i.e. permissions 660). Check out [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:Securing_database_passwords this page on MediaWiki on database password security].\n\nFurthermore, to prevent others from capturing wiki login data, the connection must be encrypted. For this purpose a SSL certificate was issued (by SRCF) which allows connection via https. The <code>.htaccess</code> file in the web root ensures that all http requests are redirected to https:\n\n<syntaxhighlight>\nRewriteEngine On\nRewriteCond %{HTTPS} !on\nRewriteRule (.*) https://%{HTTP_HOST}%{REQUEST_URI}\n</syntaxhighlight>\n\n==MediaWiki extensions==\nMediaWiki supports several extensions that reside under <code>/wiki/extensions/</code>. To install an extension, follow [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:Extensions this guide]. Currently, this wiki has the extensions [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:SyntaxHighlight SyntaxHighlight_GeSHi] and [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:CategoryTree CategoryTree] installed, as can be seen by examining <code>/wiki/LocalSettings.php</code> (or alternatively see the page [[Special:Version]]).\n\n=Backup and Restore=\n==Backup==\nIt is good practice to keep a backup of the website in case something happens to the web server. There are two parts to such a backup:\n# the files in the webroot directory and\n# the contents of our MySQL database.\nFor this purpose, the user <code>rnw29</code> wrote a simple bash script following [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:Backing_up_a_wiki#Database this guide] to create a backup and upload it to our [https://github.com/CUUASS/WebsitePlusWiki GitHub repo]. This script resides under <code>/public/societies/cuuass/scripts/</code>:\n\n<syntaxhighlight lang=\"bash\">\n#!/bin/bash\n\n# first create Database dump\necho \'$wgReadOnly = \"Dumping Database, Access will be restored shortly\"\' \\\n        >> /public/societies/cuuass/public_html/wiki/LocalSettings.php\n\n# nice -n 19 lowers the priority of the process\nnice -n 19 mysqldump -h localhost -u cuuass -p --default-character-set=binary cuuass \\\n     --password=\"outSecretMySqlPassword\" \\\n        > /public/societies/cuuass/public_html/wiki_backup/backup.sql\n\n# remove last line from LocalSettings.php which was added above\n# thus restoring write access to wiki\nsed -i \'$ d\' /public/societies/cuuass/public_html/wiki/LocalSettings.php\n\n# Now do a git commit and push to github\ncd /public/societies/cuuass/public_html/\nnice -n 19 git add -A\ngit commit -m \"This is an automatic commit, created on $(date)\"\ngit push\necho \"done\"\ncd -\n</syntaxhighlight>\n\nRemember to change <code>ourSecretMySqlPassword</code> when you copy this. Again, this script must have permissions 660 so the password is not world-readable. A [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron cronjob] was installed for <code>rnw29</code> for this script that runs every Monday at 4:30am. It is worth checking the [https://github.com/CUUASS/WebsitePlusWiki GitHub repo] to see if commits are actually being made on a weekly basis. If not, suspicion should arise!\n\nYou might be worried that the SQL dump also contains passwords of wiki users, however these passwords are [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cryptographic_hash_function hashed] using a [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salt_(cryptography) random salt], which would make it difficult for an attacker to find out the passwords.\n\n==Restore==\nTo restore the website in case of corruption, simply clone the [https://github.com/CUUASS/WebsitePlusWiki Github repo]. To restore the MySQL database, follow [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:Restoring_a_wiki_from_backup these instructions].',_binary 'utf-8'),(37,_binary 'Hello from Switzerland. I\'m glad to be here. My first name is Norberto. <br>I live in a small city called Le Petit-Saconnex in south Switzerland.<br>I was also born in Le Petit-Saconnex 35 years ago. Married in June year 2005. I\'m working at the college.<br><br>My web blog ... [http://eagar.pl/ biuro podatkowe pozna]',_binary 'utf-8'),(38,_binary 'Got nothing to write about me I think.<br>Hurrey Im here and a part of cuuass.org.<br>I really wish I am useful at all<br><br>Also visit my website - [http://viagrabuyonlines.com viagra for sale no prescription]',_binary 'utf-8'),(39,_binary 'Potenztabletten raises blood circulation in order to certain body parts as well as relaxes the entire body muscle tissue.<br>Is actually accustomed to deal with impotency inside males that may be generally referred to as erection disorder. Universal Potenztabletten Sildenafil citrate can be used to deal with pulmonary arterial hypertension as well as enhances the capacity associated with males to keep an excellent hard-on. It is usually employed for extra problems because recommended because of your health-related helper.<br><br>Viagra enhances har